==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From Latin ''Persia'' < Greek [[Περσίς]] < [[Old Persian]] ''Pārsa''.

===Proper noun===
'''Persia'''

#The [[country]] of [[Iran]] until 1935 was officially called "[[Persia]]" in English. However, the local name of the country since the Sassanian period has been "[[Iran]]". Since 1935 both terms "Iran" and "Persia" have been used in English, though [[Iran]] predominates. The [[w:Persia|Persian Empire]] once included most of Western and Central [[Asia]] and North [[Africa]].

